# CulturePulse — optional API keys
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every source below is OPTIONAL. The app runs fully on 12 free no-key
# sources without any of these. Adding a key auto-activates that source on
# the next deploy — no code change needed.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` and fill what you have.
# Production: add these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# (Never commit real keys — .env is gitignored.)

# ── YouTube Data API v3 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# India region trending videos + comment/search mining.
# Get: https://console.cloud.google.com → enable "YouTube Data API v3"
#      → Credentials → API key.  Free quota 10,000 units/day.
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=

# ── Spotify Web API (Client-Credentials flow) ────────────────────────────
# ⚠️ As of 2026 Spotify gates Web API access behind Spotify PREMIUM. A free
# account cannot tick "Web API" when creating an app, so this source stays
# dormant unless you have Premium. The music-chart lens is already covered
# free by Apple Top Songs + Last.fm below, so this is OPTIONAL.
# Get (Premium only): https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard → Create app
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Last.fm (WIRED · free, no paywall) ────────────────────────────────────
# India top tracks + top artists — the listening/tribe signal Spotify gates.
# Get: https://www.last.fm/api/account/create
LASTFM_API_KEY=

# ── Ticketmaster Discovery (WIRED · free) ─────────────────────────────────
# Live India events — concerts, festivals, shows (demand signal).
# Get: https://developer.ticketmaster.com → My Apps → Consumer Key
TICKETMASTER_API_KEY=

# ── Google Books (WIRED · free) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# What India is reading. Same Google Cloud project as YouTube — enable Books API.
GOOGLE_BOOKS_API_KEY=

# ── TMDB / The Movie Database (WIRED · free) ──────────────────────────────
# Trending movies + TV (global) + Hindi-cinema discover — OTT/film culture.
# Get: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api → request a v3 API key (instant).
TMDB_API_KEY=
